#: ../../SO2.md:335
msgid "It is important to note that changes in the proportion of population exposure to land degradation may not only be due to the expansion of land degradation but also to population growth, among other factors. For example, if 30 out of 100 people live in a land degraded area, that represents 30%. If the population increases by 10 people, all of whom settle in degraded areas, the total becomes 40 out of 110—meaning approximately 36% now live in degraded areas."
